image.altText: A silver car hits glass doors of restaurant, glass cracked and items damaged

props.synopsis: A seven-year-old boy is among four people injured when a car crashed into a restaurant in Adelaide's eastern suburbs.

title.children: Car crashes through Adelaide restaurant window and hits diners

props.synopsis: Staff and students at a regional South Australian school were intrigued to know what was on an old film found in a time capsule they dug up and the reporter assigned to look at it discovered an unexpected personal connection.

title.children: When an ABC film was found in a 50-year-old primary school time capsule it contained a surprise for one of our reporters

image.altText: A black and white class photo with a male teacher. The children's faces are blurred.

props.synopsis: A Victorian government inquiry has laid bare how the state's education department protected paedophile David MacGregor, allowing him to teach and coach children for almost three decades despite multiple warnings from children and their parents.

title.children: The horror story of paedophile teacher David MacGregor has been exposed in vivid detail

image.altText: A masked Palestinian fighter waves to an injured girl as she is helped into a vehicle

props.synopsis: Hamas releases a further 13 Israelis and four Thai nationals in a second round of swaps under a ceasefire deal.

title.children: Second group of Hamas hostages arrives in Israel, after release delayed by claims IDF violated truce

image.altText: A wide photo of a long beach, with small boats, rubble and sheets of metal on the sand. Cars drive on a road nearby

props.synopsis: Nicole Johnston, a former Gaza-based journalist, reflects on the friends she made and the conflicts she covered in the war-torn region.

title.children: Power cuts, polluted beaches and a once thriving tunnel trade. This is life in Gaza's 'open air prison'

image.altText: A man in the water on a kayak.

props.synopsis: A 47-year-old man has set the new record of 14 days, 23 hours and 33 minutes for the feat — and he did it without a phone to entertain him, after a mishap on the first day.

title.children: Phone mishap sees man break record for fastest kayak down Murray River with no entertainment

image.altText: A woman holds a photo at a rally against domestic violence.

props.synopsis: For the second time in as many days, domestic violence prevention campaigners rally in Adelaide calling for systemic reform in response to the recent deaths of four women, including Jodie Jewell who was shot dead at Modbury North.

title.children: Friend of shooting victim Jodie Jewell speaks out as advocates rally against domestic violence

image.altText: A flooded street in Naracoorte.

props.synopsis: The town of Naracoorte in South Australia's south-east breaks a longstanding local rainfall record, with a two-day deluge causing streets to flood as well damage to powerlines and several buildings.

title.children: Two-day deluge breaks rainfall records in SA regional town, BOM says

image.altText: A man in a suit holding a laptop walks past a group of photographers outside

props.synopsis: When a billionaire darling of Silicon Valley became the CEO of OpenAI and built ChatGPT, he was sure it would change the world. But in one week, the collaboration between the company's altruistic board and thriving business unravelled, leaving the industry asking just how open AI is going to be in the future.

title.children: Could an AI experiment called project Q* be the reason for the OpenAI meltdown?

image.altText: A for lease sign at a picket fence

props.synopsis: The pathway to home ownership is not as simple as it used to be, and it's not the fault of younger workers, writes Gareth Hutchens.

title.children: How are younger workers expected to compete with 'Generation Landlord'?

image.altText: Concept image of a widen road on a lower level under a large intersection with traffic going perpendicular

props.synopsis: New vision released shows the final section to be completed of the North-South Corridor upgrade as the South Australian government seeks feedback from communities.

title.children: Fresh look at 'city-defining' upgrade in one of South Australia's biggest road projects

image.altText: A woman looks out of the window of a plane.

props.synopsis: South Australian police have charged a woman over an alleged second attempt to murder a man who had already been left quadriplegic by an axe attack, with the man's former partner — who was charged over the earlier incident — also now in custody.

title.children: Woman arrested over alleged second attempt to murder axe attack victim as former partner extradited

image.altText: Australian Energy Minister Chris Bowen speaks to the media during a press conference.

props.synopsis: The government says Australia is on its way to hitting its 2030 climate targets as it faces criticism from conservation groups for support of fossil fuels.

title.children: Australia to hit 2030 emissions target, government says

image.altText: an image grab from a simulation of a driver in a car about to enter the rozelle interchange

props.synopsis: The Rozelle Interchange comprising of 16.6 kilometres of road tunnel welcomes its first lot of motorists, as drivers are warned to brace for weeks of traffic disruption and delays.

title.children: Australia's largest underground motorway maze opens in Sydney. How confusing is it to navigate?

image.altText: A crowd of people at a pro-Palestinian rally on the lawns of the State Library of Victoria, many waving flags.

props.synopsis: For the seventh week in a row, pro-Palestinian protesters gather at the State Library of Victoria, as Sydney's Jewish community is told of rise of anti-Semitism at a rally in the CBD.

title.children: Palestinian supporters take to Melbourne streets, as Sydney's Jewish community rallies in CBD

image.altText: A graphically altered image of a newspaper front page, a parcel and a post office.

props.synopsis: A newborn baby was found dead in a parcel, with police on opposite sides of Australia bewildered by who could've sent it. Now, DNA advancements are offering hope the six-decade 'baby in the post' mystery could soon be solved.

title.children: Decades after the grisly discovery of a baby in the post, could the case finally be solved?

image.altText: A drone shot of houses and a small town right near a beach

props.synopsis: Northern Territory Police say a man is dead after a fatal hit-and-run crash in Nhulunbuy this morning.

title.children: Police investigating fatal hit-and-run of cyclist in Arnhem Land community

image.altText: a large kitchen sink with a window above it

props.synopsis: The Halls family wanted to put their kitchen sink in the pantry so they could shut the door on the dishes. But moving it just a few feet cost them thousands of dollars.

title.children: They call it the $25k sink — the kitchen fitting that sank this family's chance of a HomeBuilder grant

image.altText: A photo of a person driving a car at sunset, taken from behind the driver's seat

props.synopsis: Psychologists say some Australians are cancelling their autism assessment appointments after learning they could be required to disclose their condition under Fitness to Drive standards.

title.children: Australians are cancelling autism assessments after learning a diagnosis could jeopardise their driver's licence

image.altText: Man in check shirt and light blue shorts holds up a huge fish and smiles.

props.synopsis: Fishing for bass as a teenager in the 1940s, John used some willow and a jam tin to make his own lures. Decades later, he's had great success with them.

title.children: At 91, lure maker says key to good craft is thinking like a fish

image.altText: A man with his arm around a woman, both in uniform and both looking at the camear

props.synopsis: Oleksandra and Oleksandr fight in the same Ukrainian combat unit, trying to push back invading Russian forces on the frontlines. Their bond runs even deeper than most.

title.children: This woman serves in the same front line as her father. She calls him every day to make sure he's still alive

image.altText: A man with grey hair sits with his arm around a young girl.

props.synopsis: Single father Peter Voelker is fighting to find out why his daughter Ellie, who has severe disabilities and needs constant care, suddenly lost $26,000 of support.

title.children: 'My daughter needs help now': Single father fighting to restore NDIS funding to daughter with severe disabilities

image.altText: A man with an earring, beard, braids and a shaved side of the head looks at a woman with purple hair and earrings

props.synopsis: The Sydneysider couple had planned their dream wedding at a famous movie set, but everything changed when their cruise ship failed to meet New Zealand's biohazard rules.

title.children: Couple's planned wedding ruined when P&O cruise had to be turned back from New Zealand

image.altText: a home in kendall with blue and white police tape

props.synopsis: Detectives have arrested Michael Hatzigeorgiou, 39, following an investigation into the alleged shooting murder in Kendall of a 43-year-old, who was found unresponsive in the street by members of the public.

title.children: Police charge 39-year-old man as accessory to murder after alleged fatal shooting

image.altText: A dozen men in military uniforms stand around the rim of a ship floating on water

props.synopsis: HMAS Toowoomba, who's divers sustained minor injuries from a Chinese sonar pulse, has now begun joint naval patrols in the South China Sea where regional tensions with Beijing are growing.

title.children: Australian warship involved in a Chinese sonar incident begins joint naval drills with Philippines in South China Sea

image.altText: A woman and man sit on a couch with a younger woman sitting in the middle of them

props.synopsis: Despite cultural preference for sons in some Asian societies, researchers from Monash University Malaysia found that living with daughters is positively associated with happiness in old age.

title.children: What brings happiness in old age? Researchers say it could be living with your daughter

image.altText: A middle aged man leans against a ute looking out over a completely blackened land.

props.synopsis: Sid Godwin says back-burning may have prevented a bushfire on his property where he lost 10,000 hectares of grazing land.

title.children: Excessive red tape and 'unmanaged' national parks blamed for Queensland bushfire devastation

image.altText: A tabby cat sits under a bed

props.synopsis: Women in violent and abusive relationships will often delay leaving due to concerns for the welfare of their pets, but an RSPCA program provides a safe bed for them while their owners seek refuge and safety.

title.children: Patricia was told to have bags packed ready to leave her abusive husband, but feared for her cats

image.altText: An illustration of a man and woman on a tandem bike both riding while reading a book, surrounded by books

props.synopsis: Much anticipated new works by winners of the Miles Franklin Literary Award and the Booker Prize are the books our critics couldn't put down this month.

title.children: The seven books our critics couldn't put down in November

image.altText: Courtney Bruce

props.synopsis: Super Netball stars boycott their awards night, as Diamonds players are forced to attend after Netball Australia threatens legal action.

title.children: Netball Australia confirms it threatened legal action against players as stars boycotted awards night

image.altText: Heated1

props.synopsis: Darwin Nunez and Pep Guardiola exchange heated words after Liverpool and Manchester City's draw, as Arsenal goes to the top of the EPL table.

title.children: Liverpool star in heated exchange with Manchester City manager as draw leads to new Premier League leader

image.altText: Jannik Sinner

props.synopsis: Novak Djokovic's run of 21 straight wins at the Davis Cup comes to an end as Jannik Sinner leads Italy into the final against Australia — here's how it might play out.

title.children: Djokovic's stunning Davis Cup streak ends as Italy secures showdown with Australia

image.altText: An F1 driver, in full suit and helmet, standing on his car, arms raised in celebration, while fireworks explode in the night sky

props.synopsis: Max Verstappen has won the last three races around Yas Marina, but all drivers will be keen to end the season on a positive note.

title.children: Everything you need to know about the Formula 1 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix

image.altText: Looking up at a crab being held in someone's fingertips

props.synopsis: A carpet of "tens of thousands" of crabs found bobbing in the Indian Ocean has sparked calls for better, more detailed research.

title.children: Mystery crab migration 'never seen before' off Shark Bay could be new subspecies
